summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of manufacturer interest, likely within a specific market or technology sector. The structure is a simple two-column table, listing five distinct manufacturers: IBM, Wang, Digital Equipment, AT&T, and Hewlett-Packard. Each manufacturer is associated with a percentage representing their level of interest. IBM demonstrates the highest interest at 81%, significantly exceeding the other listed companies. Wang follows with 40% interest, and Digital Equipment shows 36% interest. AT&T and Hewlett-Packard exhibit lower, comparable levels of interest at 22% and 21%, respectively. The data highlights a clear hierarchy of interest, with IBM leading and a gradual decrease in interest among the remaining manufacturers.
